&lt;p&gt;If you want to keep the &lt;code&gt;startService&lt;/code&gt; function independent of the &lt;code&gt;collection_api&lt;/code&gt; types, you can use a anonymous function in &lt;code&gt;main()&lt;/code&gt;. If you know that you what ever you are registering is always dependent on the implementation of the anonymous function (in this case &amp;amp;server.Server{}), then you can leave this detail out of the function signature of &lt;code&gt;startService&lt;/code&gt; and put it into the anonymous function: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;func startService(sr func(*grpc.Server)) error {
    lis, err := net.Listen("tcp", port)
