&lt;p&gt;In the &lt;a href="https://github.com/golang/crypto/blob/master/ssh/cipher.go#L95" rel="nofollow"&gt;source code&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;code&gt;go.crypto/ssh&lt;/code&gt; package, we can see that the supported ciphers are the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;aes128-ctr&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;aes192-ctr&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;aes256-ctr&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;arcfour128&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;arcfour256&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While freeSSHd supports:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;aes128-cbc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;aes192-cbc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;aes256-cbc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3des-cbc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;blowfish-cbc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;rijndael128-cbc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;rijndael192-cbc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;rijndael256-cbc&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;rijndael-cbc@lysator.liu.se&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because the client and server shares no common cipher, you will get the error message. The reason why CBC mode is not supported in the ssh package is most likely because of a &lt;a href="http://www.kb.cert.org/vuls/id/958563" rel="nofollow"&gt;vulnerability&lt;/a&gt;, as discussed in &lt;a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/golang-nuts/J2XCsTsNQ9o" rel="nofollow"&gt;this&lt;/a&gt;  golang-nuts thread.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A solution to your problem might be to try install a different SSH server, such as &lt;a href="http://sshwindows.sourceforge.net/" rel="nofollow"&gt;OpenSSH for Windows&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
